<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TT1.11">
<l>oppiṉai yillavaṉ pēykaḷ kūṭi yoṉṟiṉai yoṉṟaṭit tokka littup</l>
<l>pappiṉai yiṭṭup pakaṇṭai pāṭap pāṭirun tannari yāḻa maippa</l>
<l>vappaṉai yaṇitiru vālaṅ kāṭṭu ḷaṭikaḷaic ceṭitalaik kāraik kāṟpēy</l>
<l>ceppiya centamiḻ pattum vallār civakati cērntiṉpa meytu vārē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master all the ten in refinded Tamil spoken</l>
<l>by the bushy-headed demoness from Kāraikkāl on the majesty in decorative Tirvālaṅkāṭu, on the father,</l>
<l>while those jackals effect the lute, keeping singing, while owls sing, putting up the extension(?),</l>
<l>as demonesses gather, one strinking the other, shouting in joy for him who does not have his like,</l>
	<l>will join Śiva’s refuge [and] reach pleasure.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
